On July 29, 2022, the President signed into law the Desert Sage Youth Wellness Center Access Improvement Act, also known as S. 144. This law mandates the Department of Health and Human Services to obtain private land in order to enhance access to the Desert Sage Youth Wellness Center. The President expressed gratitude to Senators Feinstein and Padilla, as well as Representatives Ruiz, Calvert, Aguilar, Issa, Barragán, Cárdenas, and Mike Thompson for their leadership in this matter.